  'Your business card still says “find us on Facebook”',
  'Every time a customer says “I tried to look you up,” you feel it',
  'You spend Sundays worrying about marketing instead of resting',
  'Word-of-mouth caps your growth at whatever your last 10 customers told their friends',
  'You miss the launch-rate window — and pay up to $32/month more, every month, for the next 12',
];

const success = [
  'New customers show up saying “I found you on Google”',
  'A site that sells for you while you sleep, eat, work, or take a Sunday off',
  'A business card that earns calls instead of explanations',
  'A digital footprint your competitors can’t match without spending $5,000 and six months',
  'The growth you’ve been chasing for two years, finally compounding',
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What if I don’t like the site after I see it?',
    a: 'First, we keep editing until you do — unlimited rounds, no extra charge. Photo, copy, layout, services, anything. If you still don’t love it, you walk away: pay nothing, or get a full refund if you prepaid the $35 rate. Plus a 30-day money-back guarantee on every plan — if you change your mind within 30 days of your site going live, every dollar comes back, no questions.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Isn’t my Instagram or Facebook page enough?',
    a: 'Social media is rented land. The algorithm decides who sees you, and one change can wipe out your reach overnight. Instagram and Facebook are great for staying top-of-mind with people who already know you — but they don’t tell your full story, build deep trust, or convert strangers into paying customers the way a real website does. Your site is the foundation; social is the megaphone that points back to it.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Isn’t my Google Business Profile enough?',
    a: 'GMB gets you in the Map Pack — and we set that up for you. But it’s a listing, not a brand experience. It can’t tell your story, answer the questions in a customer’s head, or walk them through why you’re different from the next name on the list. A real website does all of that, 24/7, on autopilot. Think of Google Business as the map pin and your site as the storefront the pin points to.',
  },
  {
    q: 'I’m not tech-savvy. Will I have to figure anything out?',
    a: 'No. You text us what you do and who you serve — that’s the whole job. We handle the writing, the design, the revisions, the hosting, the domain, the SSL, Google Business, Apple Maps. Want to change something later? Send us a message. Most edits go live the same day.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How does the launch rate work?',
    a: 'Three monthly billing options — no big upfront fee, ever: (1) Prepay your first month ($35) before we start, and you lock in $35/month for the rest of your first year. (2) Pay your first month ($53) within 24 hours of delivery, and lock in $53/month for your first year. (3) Pay anytime after at the standard $67/month rate. Same site, same unlimited revisions, same 30-day money-back guarantee on every plan. The lower rates just reward earlier commitment.',
