    a: 'Because the math doesn’t favor DIY. The average solo business loses $70,000 a year to bad online presence — and most DIY sites never get finished. $35 is less than half your phone bill. Use the hours you’d spend learning Squarespace to do the work you’re actually good at.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will my site grow with my business?',
    a: 'Yes. We start with exactly what your business needs today — clear, fast, conversion-focused. As you grow, we add unlimited pages, features, bookings, blog content, e-commerce, member areas — whatever the next stage looks like. No platform rebuild, no agency-style "scope creep" fees. You text us; we build.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How is this different from Wix, Squarespace, or a freelancer?',
    a: 'It’s faster, it’s written to sell, and you don’t have to touch it. Drag-and-drop builders make sites that look like everyone else’s and load slow. Freelancers come and go. We build a site that loads instantly, says the right things, and stays up forever — and you can text us anytime.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What if I already have a website?',
    a: 'Probably means it’s not pulling its weight. Send us the link. We’ll tell you honestly whether ours would convert better — and if not, we won’t take your money.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it safe? What about viruses or hacks?',
    a: 'Yes. There’s no admin login to break into, no plugins to go out of date, no shopping cart that can leak credit cards (unless you ask for one). It’s the simplest, safest kind of website there is — built to stay up and stay clean.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Who owns the website?',
    a: 'You do. The files are emailed to you the moment you cancel — or automatically after 3 months of payments, whichever comes first. No lock-in. No platform you can’t leave.',
  },
